"title": "1180: God, wisdom of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1180",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture declares that God alone is wise and discerning, and that human wisdom is often unable or unwilling to understand his ways. God's wisdom is expressed in both creation and redemption.</p>\n<h2>God's wisdom described</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:29\">ISA 28:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:3\">1SA 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:27\">ROM 16:27</a></p>\n<h3>God's wisdom is beyond measure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:5\">PSA 147:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:7\">ISA 44:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:7\">JER 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:33\">ROM 11:33</a></p>\n<h3>God's wisdom is profound</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:28\">ISA 40:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:4\">JOB 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:12-Job28:24\">JOB 28:12–28:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:5\">PSA 92:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:17\">ECC 8:17</a></p>\n<h3>God's wisdom is superior to human wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:9\">ISA 55:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:22\">JOB 21:22</a></p>\n<h2>God's wisdom exhibited</h2>\n<h3>God's wisdom in creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:12\">JER 10:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:25-Job28:27\">JOB 28:25–28:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:14-Job37:16\">JOB 37:14–37:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:24\">PSA 104:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:5\">PSA 136:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:19-Prov3:20\">PRO 3:19–3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:12-Isa40:14\">ISA 40:12–40:14</a></p>\n<h3>God's wisdom as an agent in creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:22-Prov8:31\">PRO 8:22–8:31</a></strong> <em>Wisdom here is given personality, and may refer to the pre-incarnate Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h3>God's wisdom in historical events</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:2\">ISA 31:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:13-Job12:25\">JOB 12:13–12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:20-Dan2:22\">DAN 2:20–2:22</a></p>\n<h3>God's wisdom in knowing the human mind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:2\">PSA 139:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:4\">PSA 139:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:6\">PSA 139:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ the wisdom of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6\">ISA 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:2\">ISA 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:24\">1CO 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:2-Col2:3\">COL 2:2–2:3</a></p>\n<h2>God's wisdom in the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:25\">1CO 1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:18-1Cor1:21\">1CO 1:18–1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10\">EPH 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>God gives his wisdom to human beings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:17\">EPH 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:11-2Chr1:12\">2CH 1:11–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:25\">EZR 7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:6\">PRO 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:11\">ECC 12:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:23\">DAN 2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:6-1Cor2:16\">1CO 2:6–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:5\">JAS 1:5</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of God's wisdom</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:28\">1KI 3:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:24-Isa28:29\">ISA 28:24–28:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:49\">LUK 11:49</a></p>",
